1
00:00:00,240 --> 00:00:01,400
If he wants to play this game,

2
00:00:01,400 --> 00:00:02,160
we’ll play, too.

3
00:00:02,160 --> 00:00:03,240
And we’ll win.

4
00:00:03,280 --> 00:00:04,160
What do you mean?

5
00:00:04,160 --> 00:00:07,840
Convince him to get a divorce
and give you back everything.

6
00:00:07,880 --> 00:00:08,360
Use me.
What?

7
00:00:09,040 --> 00:00:11,120
Use me to fake an affair.

8
00:00:11,920 --> 00:00:12,760
Get away from me!

9
00:00:13,200 --> 00:00:14,200
He’s the only man I love.

10
00:00:14,280 --> 00:00:15,360
I’m faithful to North.

11
00:00:15,480 --> 00:00:16,800
I don’t want to live like this anymore.

12
00:00:17,040 --> 00:00:18,480
I want to step down
from my role at Empire.

13
00:00:18,680 --> 00:00:19,200
What?

14
00:00:19,560 --> 00:00:20,960
Maybe we can start
a gated community project.

15
00:00:21,160 --> 00:00:22,160
I just want to be with you, Tim.

16
00:00:25,440 --> 00:00:28,640
I don’t know what I’m feeling.

17
00:00:29,440 --> 00:00:31,000
My head is a mess.

18
00:00:32,920 --> 00:00:34,600
I don’t even know

19
00:00:37,320 --> 00:00:38,520
if I still love you.

20
00:00:45,200 --> 00:00:48,600
Well, shall we find out?

21
00:01:32,920 --> 00:01:34,240
I don’t feel a thing.

22
00:01:39,120 --> 00:01:40,200
What are you smiling at?

23
00:01:40,600 --> 00:01:41,320
Nothing.

24
00:01:42,320 --> 00:01:42,920
I’m gone.

25
00:01:43,120 --> 00:01:44,000
Hold on.

26
00:01:44,520 --> 00:01:45,240
North.

27
00:01:46,960 --> 00:01:48,840
I’ll do whatever it takes
for you to love me again.

28
00:02:56,840 --> 00:03:02,160
GRANDPA

29
00:03:09,360 --> 00:03:10,400
Hello.

30
00:03:10,840 --> 00:03:11,440
(Pai.)

31
00:03:12,240 --> 00:03:13,600
(Is everything alright with North?)

32
00:03:13,720 --> 00:03:16,040
(I barely see him this week.)

33
00:03:16,400 --> 00:03:17,880
(He rarely picks up the phone.)

34
00:03:19,360 --> 00:03:22,360
North… is a little under the weather.

35
00:03:22,360 --> 00:03:24,160
He probably just doesn't want you
to get sick, too, Grandpa.

36
00:03:24,720 --> 00:03:25,560
Is that so?

37
00:03:26,520 --> 00:03:31,440
(Well, then, will you please give him
a basket of fruits for me?)

38
00:03:31,960 --> 00:03:34,080
How is his bakery doing?

39
00:03:34,720 --> 00:03:35,760
Any progress?

40
00:03:37,800 --> 00:03:38,760
To tell you the truth,

41
00:03:39,840 --> 00:03:42,640
it’s like North didn’t learn anything
this past whole year.

42
00:03:43,480 --> 00:03:44,600
(Is that right?)

43
00:03:45,160 --> 00:03:49,120
Would you mind looking over
this matter, Pai?

44
00:03:49,960 --> 00:03:52,960
(If North really can’t get by, like you said,)

45
00:03:53,640 --> 00:03:58,320
maybe it’s time for him to come back
and learn something at Empire.

46
00:04:00,760 --> 00:04:01,840
Of course, Grandpa.

47
00:04:24,520 --> 00:04:25,520
Are you still in pain?

48
00:04:25,960 --> 00:04:26,760
I completely forgot.

49
00:04:28,280 --> 00:04:29,160
I’m okay now.

50
00:04:29,480 --> 00:04:30,400
You can hug me all you want.

51
00:04:38,000 --> 00:04:39,080
Are you still tired?

52
00:04:39,720 --> 00:04:41,360
Why don’t you sleep in
for 10 more minutes?

53
00:04:44,480 --> 00:04:45,520
I can’t.

54
00:04:46,800 --> 00:04:49,800
I have so many things to do today.

55
00:04:50,320 --> 00:04:54,480
Grandpa was just on the phone,
telling me to handle North’s bakery.

56
00:04:54,800 --> 00:04:57,880
Good thing he didn’t scold me for
taking time off to take care of you.

57
00:04:59,640 --> 00:05:00,840
I’m sorry.

58
00:05:00,880 --> 00:05:04,480
If I didn’t get hurt, you wouldn’t have
to waste all this time to be with me.

59
00:05:05,520 --> 00:05:06,160
It’s alright.
I’m happy to do it.

60
00:05:10,200 --> 00:05:14,680
Do you remember my friend Kuea who
works on a gated community project?

61
00:05:16,520 --> 00:05:17,120
Yes.

62
00:05:17,680 --> 00:05:21,520
I have an appointment with him
this afternoon.

63
00:05:22,120 --> 00:05:23,160
I want you to come with me.

64
00:05:25,720 --> 00:05:26,120
Alright.

65
00:05:28,440 --> 00:05:30,600
I’ll have Nana send you the location.

66
00:05:31,200 --> 00:05:33,720
I have to get something done
in the morning.

67
00:05:36,000 --> 00:05:36,440
Of course.

68
00:05:36,800 --> 00:05:37,600
I’ll go take a shower.

69
00:05:57,600 --> 00:05:58,520
Stop it!

70
00:06:16,640 --> 00:06:17,560
Surprise.

71
00:06:20,960 --> 00:06:22,720
North, do you like it?

72
00:06:23,760 --> 00:06:24,920
It’s adorable.

73
00:06:25,760 --> 00:06:29,120
But what money did you buy it with?

74
00:06:30,120 --> 00:06:32,680
Is it the 250 million I gave you?

75
00:06:34,040 --> 00:06:34,760
Yes.

76
00:06:36,200 --> 00:06:37,480
North, North, North!

77
00:06:37,640 --> 00:06:38,840
North, calm down!

78
00:06:40,600 --> 00:06:42,600
This trick would have worked,

79
00:06:43,200 --> 00:06:45,480
if I didn’t know you’re a con man.

80
00:06:46,360 --> 00:06:46,760
North.

81
00:07:21,440 --> 00:07:22,000
So…

82
00:07:23,200 --> 00:07:24,320
How are things on your end?

83
00:07:25,760 --> 00:07:28,560
I think North still has feelings for me.

84
00:07:28,640 --> 00:07:29,240
But?

85
00:07:29,760 --> 00:07:33,880
But… he’s in denial that he does.

86
00:07:36,720 --> 00:07:42,000
Honestly, recently, he kissed me.

87
00:07:42,200 --> 00:07:44,560
I knew right away that he still likes me,

88
00:07:44,880 --> 00:07:46,200
but he wouldn’t admit it.

89
00:07:47,680 --> 00:07:51,160
So I plan to make him
fall in love with me again.

90
00:07:51,240 --> 00:07:53,320
Is that what the balloons
and flowers are for?

91
00:07:54,760 --> 00:07:55,280
Yes.

92
00:07:58,000 --> 00:07:59,080
Listen to me, U.

93
00:08:00,080 --> 00:08:05,280
This simple trick would work
if he didn’t know you’re a scammer.

94
00:08:07,680 --> 00:08:08,880
Then what should I do?

95
00:08:09,400 --> 00:08:13,440
You have to do what he wants deep down
without having to ask.

96
00:08:15,600 --> 00:08:16,160
Such as?

97
00:08:18,480 --> 00:08:19,360
Such as…

98
00:08:20,400 --> 00:08:21,960
Taking care of him,

99
00:08:23,080 --> 00:08:25,000
being there for him
when he needs someone.

100
00:08:25,320 --> 00:08:28,760
And do it effortlessly.

101
00:08:29,440 --> 00:08:31,160
Make it seem as normal as possible.

102
00:08:34,200 --> 00:08:34,840
That’s profound.

103
00:08:35,320 --> 00:08:37,920
Where did you learn all this?

104
00:08:44,920 --> 00:08:48,200
I just… watch and learn.

105
00:08:50,360 --> 00:08:51,000
Let’s talk about you.

106
00:08:52,200 --> 00:08:54,000
Are you sure you want
to do this with North?

107
00:08:57,120 --> 00:08:59,160
I don’t want to keep living like this.

108
00:08:59,760 --> 00:09:03,360
How can you be sure he will forgive you when he knows who you are now?

109
00:09:03,640 --> 00:09:04,760
What choice do I have
when I’m already in love with him?

110
00:09:05,840 --> 00:09:09,880
There’s nothing else I can do but my best.

111
00:09:31,240 --> 00:09:32,960
North, it’s me.

112
00:09:33,120 --> 00:09:33,720
Are you home?

113
00:09:34,680 --> 00:09:35,320
Go hide.

114
00:09:36,080 --> 00:09:36,880
Go and hide!
Hide!

115
00:09:38,640 --> 00:09:39,360
Why?

116
00:09:39,880 --> 00:09:41,400
Just hide if you don’t want to die.

117
00:09:42,000 --> 00:09:43,160
Are you worried about me?

118
00:09:43,600 --> 00:09:44,320
Go on!

119
00:09:45,400 --> 00:09:47,680
Are you home? What’s taking so long?

120
00:09:52,080 --> 00:09:52,960
I’m here.

121
00:09:57,120 --> 00:09:58,120
I was naked.
Is U here?

122
00:10:01,760 --> 00:10:02,400
No, Pai.

123
00:10:06,680 --> 00:10:08,320
Why are you giving me this?

124
00:10:10,520 --> 00:10:11,640
Grandpa asked me to.

125
00:10:13,120 --> 00:10:13,760
Okay.

126
00:10:18,960 --> 00:10:20,120
What’s with the dog crate?

127
00:10:20,920 --> 00:10:21,960
Do you have a dog now?

128
00:10:22,720 --> 00:10:24,400
You can barely take care of yourself
and you want to have a pet?

129
00:10:26,520 --> 00:10:27,960
That’s where U sleeps.

130
00:10:29,520 --> 00:10:30,000
Good.

131
00:10:35,720 --> 00:10:39,280
Why… are you here to see me?

132
00:10:41,680 --> 00:10:44,160
I’m here to ask you
how you’re doing on the divorce.

133
00:10:47,240 --> 00:10:48,240
It’s…

134
00:10:48,640 --> 00:10:49,920
I’m gathering evidence.

135
00:10:50,600 --> 00:10:52,240
I’m–I’m almost done.

136
00:10:53,080 --> 00:10:54,800
You have to take this seriously.

137
00:10:55,080 --> 00:10:57,200
Give U a reason to want a divorce.

138
00:10:57,800 --> 00:10:58,440
Don’t cave in.
Do you understand?

139
00:11:02,600 --> 00:11:03,080
Okay.

140
00:11:05,440 --> 00:11:07,960
Anything else?

141
00:11:09,160 --> 00:11:11,480
I just went through
your bakery’s financial report.

142
00:11:12,920 --> 00:11:14,440
All this time,

143
00:11:14,920 --> 00:11:17,720
your bakery never made profits at all
since its opening.

144
00:11:18,880 --> 00:11:20,960
If we let it go on like this,
it will only get worse from here.

145
00:11:21,800 --> 00:11:23,000
I talked to Grandpa.

146
00:11:24,440 --> 00:11:25,320
We want you to shut it down.

147
00:11:27,240 --> 00:11:28,760
You’re going to work at Empire.

148
00:11:29,320 --> 00:11:31,000
I’ll be keeping my eye on you at all times.

149
00:11:32,880 --> 00:11:34,400
I hope you understand what I’m saying.

150
00:12:20,720 --> 00:12:22,560
Oh, hey, there.

151
00:12:23,760 --> 00:12:24,520
How are things?

152
00:12:25,480 --> 00:12:26,200
You talked things out with U yet?

153
00:12:26,560 --> 00:12:27,280
Everything okay now?

154
00:12:30,240 --> 00:12:30,680
What?

155
00:12:31,800 --> 00:12:32,640
What happened?

156
00:12:33,000 --> 00:12:36,720
Did U tell you he’s actually a millionaire
who’s been testing you?

157
00:12:38,360 --> 00:12:42,000
Or did your grandpa finally
tell you you were adopted?

158
00:12:42,240 --> 00:12:43,040
No!

159
00:12:43,880 --> 00:12:46,160
What do you mean, “adopted”?

160
00:12:46,600 --> 00:12:47,240
I don’t know.

161
00:12:47,560 --> 00:12:49,840
You just don’t look like your grandfather
so I assumed.

162
00:12:50,840 --> 00:12:51,840
Don’t you ever wonder

163
00:12:52,520 --> 00:12:54,400
that maybe you’re the son
of a housemaid?

164
00:12:54,400 --> 00:12:55,640
I’m not adopted!

165
00:12:59,200 --> 00:13:01,720
Then what are you so unhappy about?

166
00:13:02,640 --> 00:13:03,120
It’s…

167
00:13:04,840 --> 00:13:07,960
Pai went through our bakery’s
financial report

168
00:13:09,240 --> 00:13:11,920
and saw that we’ve been making
loss after loss.

169
00:13:13,480 --> 00:13:16,160
He told me to shut this place down
and work for him.

170
00:13:19,240 --> 00:13:28,320
I guess it’s time to accept the fact that
I’m a loser.

171
00:13:32,080 --> 00:13:33,600
You don’t need to blame yourself like that.

172
00:13:33,840 --> 00:13:34,880
He’s right—Wait.

173
00:13:37,280 --> 00:13:38,360
What are you doing here?

174
00:13:39,360 --> 00:13:41,280
I followed you.

175
00:13:43,000 --> 00:13:44,880
How long have you been here?

176
00:13:45,680 --> 00:13:48,440
Since Pure said
you were the son of a housemaid.

177
00:13:48,840 --> 00:13:50,120
I’m not!

178
00:13:52,160 --> 00:13:53,200
What are you smiling at?

179
00:13:55,320 --> 00:13:55,640
North.

180
00:13:56,440 --> 00:13:59,400
Between us, it wasn’t your fault.

181
00:13:59,920 --> 00:14:01,520
It’s not right to blame yourself.

182
00:14:03,360 --> 00:14:05,480
But this place isn’t minting money anyway.

183
00:14:06,320 --> 00:14:07,480
I still have to shut it down.

184
00:14:10,160 --> 00:14:13,720
Why don’t we give it one more try?

185
00:14:14,280 --> 00:14:16,680
One last time. One last chance.

186
00:14:18,600 --> 00:14:19,600
“We”?

187
00:14:20,640 --> 00:14:21,080
Yes

188
00:14:21,640 --> 00:14:22,320
I’ll help you.

189
00:14:57,960 --> 00:14:58,440
Pai.
Oh, Tim.

190
00:15:00,480 --> 00:15:01,280
Hello, Tim.

191
00:15:02,200 --> 00:15:04,240
We didn’t get to be properly
introduced last time.

192
00:15:04,840 --> 00:15:05,560
I’m Kuea.

193
00:15:06,360 --> 00:15:07,360
I’m Pai’s friend.

194
00:15:10,120 --> 00:15:10,840
I’m Tim.

195
00:15:11,600 --> 00:15:12,480
His boyfriend.

196
00:15:12,960 --> 00:15:15,080
We’re getting married.

197
00:15:15,600 --> 00:15:16,080
Right.

198
00:15:19,880 --> 00:15:22,760
I want to introduce you two because I think
it’s best we all get to know each other,

199
00:15:23,040 --> 00:15:25,640
seeing as we’ll be working as a team now.

200
00:15:25,840 --> 00:15:26,160
Right.

201
00:15:26,640 --> 00:15:29,520
I talked to Pai last time about
this gated community project,

202
00:15:30,200 --> 00:15:31,200
and this is the piece of land I had in mind.

203
00:15:31,800 --> 00:15:34,280
It’s been an empty land
since I was in high school.

204
00:15:34,960 --> 00:15:35,520
You’re right.

205
00:15:36,160 --> 00:15:36,840
It’s close to our school.
Yes.

206
00:15:37,800 --> 00:15:40,560
You know this neighborhood
has everything.

207
00:15:41,080 --> 00:15:41,880
It’s the perfect spot.

208
00:15:42,400 --> 00:15:45,720
I didn’t even remember there’s
a piece of land like this around our

209
00:15:46,520 --> 00:15:47,760
Reminds me of the good old times.

210
00:15:48,400 --> 00:15:50,480
This kinda makes me want some
mini pancakes from Jeab’s.

211
00:15:50,640 --> 00:15:52,000
Oh, you’re right.

212
00:15:52,280 --> 00:15:53,880
I heard that place is still open.

213
00:15:54,120 --> 00:15:54,680
Really?

214
00:15:55,080 --> 00:15:55,800
Maybe we should—

215
00:15:58,960 --> 00:16:03,360
Shall we stop talking about the past
and focus on the present?

216
00:16:03,960 --> 00:16:06,600
Speaking of which, Pai,
this piece of land sure is lovely.

217
00:16:06,920 --> 00:16:09,680
We can build a house here
after we get married.

218
00:16:09,960 --> 00:16:12,440
I’ll buy mini pancakes at Jeab’s
for you every day.

219
00:16:13,600 --> 00:16:14,960
Are you hot?

220
00:16:15,880 --> 00:16:16,760
Do you want to stand in the shades?

221
00:16:17,080 --> 00:16:19,400
You have more appointments
in the evening.

222
00:16:19,800 --> 00:16:23,200
Excuse us, we have to sort out
a lot of things about the wedding.

223
00:16:23,440 --> 00:16:24,440
Pai and I are getting marri—
Yes.

224
00:16:25,640 --> 00:16:26,440
You said that, Tim.

225
00:16:28,160 --> 00:16:28,640
Right.

226
00:16:31,640 --> 00:16:32,040
Kuea.

227
00:16:33,040 --> 00:16:34,720
Can I talk to my boyfriend for a second?

228
00:16:36,600 --> 00:16:37,320
By all means.

229
00:16:45,600 --> 00:16:46,440
Where are we going?

230
00:16:50,560 --> 00:16:51,200
What’s wrong with you?

231
00:16:51,520 --> 00:16:52,560
Nothing’s wrong with me.

232
00:16:52,800 --> 00:16:53,600
What’s wrong with Kuea?

233
00:16:53,800 --> 00:16:54,760
Nothing’s wrong with Kuea.

234
00:16:55,160 --> 00:16:56,120
It’s you.

235
00:17:01,240 --> 00:17:01,680
Are you being jealous?

236
00:17:03,320 --> 00:17:04,360
No, I’m not!

237
00:17:04,880 --> 00:17:07,080
I was just telling Kuea
we’re getting married.

238
00:17:07,880 --> 00:17:08,280
What?

239
00:17:08,840 --> 00:17:10,520
You don’t want people to know
we’re getting—

240
00:17:10,520 --> 00:17:11,080
Baby.

241
00:17:13,320 --> 00:17:17,040
I really want to do this project with you.

242
00:17:19,080 --> 00:17:20,680
But we need Kuea’s help.

243
00:17:21,240 --> 00:17:23,840
He’s in this industry
and more experienced than we are.

244
00:17:24,480 --> 00:17:26,160
I want you to respect him.

245
00:17:28,960 --> 00:17:30,800
But you didn’t need to bring up
Jeab’s mini pancakes.

246
00:17:30,800 --> 00:17:31,320
Hey.

247
00:17:33,960 --> 00:17:34,360
I’m sorry.

248
00:17:43,240 --> 00:17:43,960
You’re not jealous anymore?

249
00:17:52,400 --> 00:17:53,160
I’m not jealous anymore.

250
00:17:54,120 --> 00:17:56,400
I’m all yours, alright?

251
00:17:58,400 --> 00:17:59,160
Alright.

252
00:18:00,720 --> 00:18:04,440
Did you take your blazer off?
You’re ruining the collars.

253
00:18:05,200 --> 00:18:07,280
Did you take it off for that Kuea jerk?

254
00:18:08,480 --> 00:18:09,360
You just said you’re not jealous anymore.

255
00:18:10,320 --> 00:18:10,720
I’m not.

256
00:18:10,720 --> 00:18:11,880
I’m just asking.

257
00:18:21,920 --> 00:18:24,640
What you’re holding is the
initial report on this piece of land,

258
00:18:24,640 --> 00:18:30,000
including deeds verification, possession
history, land survey, and other things.

259
00:18:31,240 --> 00:18:31,960
Is it okay?

260
00:18:32,720 --> 00:18:34,520
Did you check whether this is
in the expropriation zone?

261
00:18:34,920 --> 00:18:37,000
I’ll check again with the DPT.

262
00:18:37,680 --> 00:18:39,240
As long as it’s not
in the expropriation zone,

263
00:18:39,240 --> 00:18:41,680
I have nothing against the rest of it.

264
00:18:42,600 --> 00:18:44,880
I’ll send all the numbers to Pai later.

265
00:18:45,400 --> 00:18:47,400
As for the supervising architect
for this project,

266
00:18:47,720 --> 00:18:49,760
Pai said you’d be in charge.

267
00:18:53,240 --> 00:18:57,280
I’ll wait for your proposal
so we can all see the picture.

268
00:18:57,800 --> 00:18:59,240
Oh, it’s…

269
00:19:00,760 --> 00:19:06,240
Can I have some time to consider

270
00:19:18,680 --> 00:19:19,440
Of course.

271
00:19:34,920 --> 00:19:37,200
OUR LAST DAY IN BUSINESS
BUY 1 GET 5 FREE

272
00:19:56,520 --> 00:19:58,160
Does he really have
a degree in marketing?

273
00:20:11,120 --> 00:20:18,760
OUR LAST DAY IN BUSINESS
BUY 4 GET 1 FREE

274
00:20:23,000 --> 00:20:23,920
What would you like?

275
00:20:24,680 --> 00:20:26,640
Any recommendations?

276
00:20:27,120 --> 00:20:29,440
Everything’s good, ma’am.

277
00:20:29,600 --> 00:20:33,720
Then, can I try this one?

278
00:20:35,120 --> 00:20:35,800
This one?

279
00:20:37,080 --> 00:20:38,880
This is too bad.

280
00:20:39,000 --> 00:20:40,600
But I’m taken.

281
00:20:43,040 --> 00:20:44,680
Let me pick something else for you.

282
00:20:44,880 --> 00:20:46,200
I’m sure you’ll like it.

283
00:20:46,840 --> 00:20:47,400
Of course.
Alright.

284
00:20:53,200 --> 00:20:54,080
That’s more than enough.

285
00:20:54,600 --> 00:20:55,240
Yes, ma’am.

286
00:20:57,000 --> 00:20:59,800
North, get the bread out
of the oven for me.

287
00:20:59,800 --> 00:21:00,800
I don’t wanna burn it.

288
00:21:03,400 --> 00:21:03,920
Ploy.

289
00:21:10,800 --> 00:21:11,120
North!

290
00:21:12,000 --> 00:21:12,480
North.

291
00:21:13,320 --> 00:21:13,920
Are you alright?

292
00:21:17,080 --> 00:21:17,840
Are you hurt?

293
00:21:18,920 --> 00:21:19,600
Not badly.

294
00:21:20,240 --> 00:21:20,760
Okay.

295
00:21:29,600 --> 00:21:30,120
Pure.

296
00:21:30,760 --> 00:21:31,520
Take over for a bit.

297
00:21:32,080 --> 00:21:32,720
I’ll take a look at North.

298
00:21:33,880 --> 00:21:34,360
Of course.

299
00:21:49,680 --> 00:21:50,480
Thank you.

300
00:21:52,520 --> 00:21:54,240
Why don’t you man the cashier?

301
00:21:54,520 --> 00:21:57,400
Don’t get too close
to the oven again, alright?

302
00:21:59,640 --> 00:22:01,040
Yeah. I know that.

303
00:22:14,840 --> 00:22:17,160
(For almost a year,)

304
00:22:17,520 --> 00:22:20,240
(this little bakery has been
a safe space for me and Pure)

305
00:22:20,720 --> 00:22:22,800
(to hide away from the busy world.)

306
00:22:23,480 --> 00:22:27,000
(We’re happy that our little bakery
has put a smile on your face.)

307
00:22:27,400 --> 00:22:35,760
But it is time for us to face the music today.

308
00:22:40,600 --> 00:22:42,200
Now that I’m shutting the place down,

309
00:22:42,960 --> 00:22:44,240
I can’t help but have this sinking feeling.

310
00:22:48,120 --> 00:22:48,520
It’s okay.

311
00:22:48,520 --> 00:22:50,600
Oh! It’s green!

312
00:22:51,400 --> 00:22:53,720
The number in the report is now green!

313
00:22:54,120 --> 00:22:55,200
Look. Look.

314
00:22:58,160 --> 00:22:58,960
Green!

315
00:23:01,800 --> 00:23:03,280
We’re making a profit!

316
00:23:12,280 --> 00:23:12,920
Hold on.

317
00:23:13,760 --> 00:23:14,720
260 baht.

318
00:23:14,960 --> 00:23:16,040
That’s just today, right?

319
00:23:16,160 --> 00:23:17,760
At least it’s a profit!

320
00:23:17,880 --> 00:23:21,560
Since we’ve been open almost a year ago,
we never had a day like this.

321
00:23:22,720 --> 00:23:24,160
Does that mean we don’t have
to close this place down?

322
00:23:24,160 --> 00:23:24,960
We can keep going!

323
00:23:26,960 --> 00:23:28,200
But… it’s just today?

324
00:23:28,400 --> 00:23:28,840
Yes!

325
00:23:29,040 --> 00:23:30,720
All Pai wants is proof!

326
00:23:30,720 --> 00:23:31,200
Yes!

327
00:23:31,280 --> 00:23:33,000
I just have to keep it going
like this for a month.

328
00:23:33,120 --> 00:23:37,600
And we’ll throw our financial report
in Pai’s face and say,

329
00:23:37,600 --> 00:23:40,400
“I can make it on my own!”

330
00:23:40,400 --> 00:23:42,720
On our own!

331
00:23:45,080 --> 00:23:46,240
Good. Good.

332
00:23:59,200 --> 00:24:00,960
Itadakimasu!

333
00:24:12,440 --> 00:24:13,360
Wanna sit with me?

334
00:24:15,760 --> 00:24:16,360
Yes.

335
00:24:32,680 --> 00:24:34,480
Thank you for today.

336
00:24:38,600 --> 00:24:40,200
I barely did anything.

337
00:24:40,880 --> 00:24:43,520
It’s all thanks to your own effort, North.

338
00:24:46,840 --> 00:24:47,800
I’ll give you all of these.

339
00:24:48,800 --> 00:24:49,760
Your favorite dumplings.

340
00:24:52,520 --> 00:24:53,520
Some pork, too.

341
00:24:54,840 --> 00:24:56,240
You have nothing left in your bowl.

342
00:24:56,240 --> 00:24:56,880
It’s alright.

343
00:24:56,880 --> 00:24:58,000
I use the wrong end of the chopsticks.

344
00:24:59,760 --> 00:25:02,280
I’m too full to go back
to the bakery for the car.

345
00:25:03,120 --> 00:25:03,680
Oh?

346
00:25:04,720 --> 00:25:07,280
How about this?

347
00:25:13,480 --> 00:25:15,160
What, U?

348
00:25:15,640 --> 00:25:17,880
I totally didn’t expect a motorcycle.

349
00:25:21,160 --> 00:25:23,840
I promise to ride safely.

350
00:25:24,960 --> 00:25:25,480
Alright?

351
00:25:36,160 --> 00:25:36,760
Let’s go.

352
00:25:52,400 --> 00:25:53,120
Here.

353
00:25:55,240 --> 00:25:55,960
Hold on to me.

354
00:26:03,680 --> 00:26:04,760
You’re so…

355
00:26:17,560 --> 00:26:19,200
Why are you flexing your muscles?

356
00:26:19,600 --> 00:26:20,440
Let’s go.

357
00:26:21,280 --> 00:26:23,080
I wasn’t even flexing, though.

358
00:26:23,360 --> 00:26:24,600
Just go.

359
00:26:24,600 --> 00:26:25,400
Alright.

360
00:26:27,240 --> 00:26:28,000
Ready?

361
00:26:39,080 --> 00:26:39,640
We’re here.

362
00:26:45,000 --> 00:26:45,480
Let me help.

363
00:27:36,200 --> 00:27:36,680
Hey!

364
00:27:38,800 --> 00:27:39,360
North!

365
00:27:40,240 --> 00:27:40,520
North!

366
00:27:41,360 --> 00:27:41,640
North!

367
00:27:47,360 --> 00:27:48,200
What was that?

368
00:28:00,320 --> 00:28:03,200
DO NOT FALL FOR THE TARGET
AT ALL COSTS!

369
00:28:34,800 --> 00:28:38,600
Are you… secretly rich?

370
00:28:40,800 --> 00:28:41,520
Come on in.

371
00:28:49,640 --> 00:28:51,400
My family was dirt poor when I was a kid.

372
00:28:52,480 --> 00:28:55,200
All three of us used to live in
a tiny one-room flat.

373
00:28:57,440 --> 00:29:00,880
But my parents gritted their teeth
and worked hard to save up

374
00:29:02,040 --> 00:29:03,280
until they had a sum of money.

375
00:29:04,880 --> 00:29:07,800
They invested in a direct marketing
business and made a killing.

376
00:29:09,280 --> 00:29:11,400
They had money to buy this house,

377
00:29:13,120 --> 00:29:15,400
asked for more loans,
and expanded their business.

378
00:29:19,320 --> 00:29:20,280
But one day, they hit a roadblock.

379
00:29:21,560 --> 00:29:22,880
Papa. Mama.

380
00:29:23,960 --> 00:29:24,800
I got a job.

381
00:29:26,160 --> 00:29:27,840
Papa? Mama?

382
00:29:30,920 --> 00:29:31,480
Hello.

383
00:29:34,280 --> 00:29:36,360
(Tim, it’s your Mama.)

384
00:29:37,360 --> 00:29:39,800
(Your Papa and I are in China.)

385
00:29:42,640 --> 00:29:46,040
(Our family won’t be the same
from now on.)

386
00:29:52,120 --> 00:29:53,560
My mother left me some money.

387
00:29:54,800 --> 00:29:56,560
She told me to sell this house.

388
00:29:58,280 --> 00:29:59,160
But I couldn’t.

389
00:30:00,160 --> 00:30:00,600
Why not?

390
00:30:00,600 --> 00:30:03,280
I want my family to come back
and live here with me.

391
00:30:03,680 --> 00:30:04,800
Tim, you idiot.

392
00:30:05,280 --> 00:30:06,320
What was that for?

393
00:30:07,400 --> 00:30:08,520
For being a stubborn idiot.

394
00:30:09,520 --> 00:30:12,880
Selling this house would pay back
at least half of your debt.

395
00:30:12,880 --> 00:30:14,520
I’m not selling it.

396
00:30:15,000 --> 00:30:16,120
I’m never going to sell it.

397
00:30:19,240 --> 00:30:22,120
What did you call me here for, then?

398
00:30:24,520 --> 00:30:25,600
I need advice.

399
00:30:25,800 --> 00:30:26,400
About what?

400
00:30:38,600 --> 00:30:41,520
Since I was a kid,
I wanted to be an architect.

401
00:30:42,480 --> 00:30:43,920
But when my family went bankrupt,

402
00:30:45,040 --> 00:30:46,320
I pressed pause on that dream.

403
00:30:51,200 --> 00:30:54,080
But then Pai offered me this supervising
architect role for his gated community.

404
00:30:54,400 --> 00:30:54,920
He did?

405
00:30:55,640 --> 00:30:57,160
Did you say yes?

406
00:31:07,080 --> 00:31:07,560
Da Zhan.

407
00:31:09,360 --> 00:31:10,000
Da Zhan.

408
00:31:19,600 --> 00:31:20,520
Da Zhan, dear.

409
00:31:23,840 --> 00:31:24,480
Yes, Pai?

410
00:31:24,800 --> 00:31:25,880
Where’s Aunt Kia?

411
00:31:26,520 --> 00:31:27,360
Isn’t she with you?

412
00:31:41,960 --> 00:31:43,920
What if I ruined everything
and I have nothing left?

413
00:31:47,840 --> 00:31:48,920
I made up my mind.

414
00:32:09,160 --> 00:32:10,640
It’s your dream, right?

415
00:32:11,560 --> 00:32:12,880
I do have a degree in architecture.

416
00:32:13,080 --> 00:32:15,800
But I have never worked in that field
since I graduated.

417
00:32:16,200 --> 00:32:17,480
It’s risky for the operation.

418
00:32:17,840 --> 00:32:19,280
If this plan to marry Pai falls through,

419
00:32:19,560 --> 00:32:22,040
I’ll never get to bring my parents
back to this house.

420
00:32:26,960 --> 00:32:29,440
Then stick to your plan.

421
00:32:30,160 --> 00:32:31,440
Marry him and divorce him.

422
00:32:32,240 --> 00:32:33,800
Do everything the way you've planned it.

423
00:32:35,760 --> 00:32:36,640
But…

424
00:32:36,840 --> 00:32:38,640
But you don’t want to anymore, do you?

425
00:32:53,160 --> 00:32:53,720
Baby.

426
00:32:54,880 --> 00:32:56,000
What are you doing sitting here all alone?

427
00:32:59,000 --> 00:33:00,040
I’m just thinking.

428
00:33:02,440 --> 00:33:04,160
You can talk to me, you know?

429
00:33:07,200 --> 00:33:07,880
It’s nothing.

430
00:33:20,760 --> 00:33:21,720
Long day, baby?

431
00:33:23,560 --> 00:33:24,360
Yeah.

432
00:33:27,040 --> 00:33:28,280
After meeting up with you,

433
00:33:29,720 --> 00:33:31,200
Grandpa came to the office to see me.

434
00:33:34,880 --> 00:33:36,760
What did he say?

435
00:33:39,760 --> 00:33:41,040
We had a huge fight.

436
00:33:42,760 --> 00:33:43,400
Because…

437
00:33:51,760 --> 00:33:53,680
I told him I wanted to quit as the CEO.

438
00:33:56,840 --> 00:33:57,960
I made up my mind.

439
00:34:00,440 --> 00:34:02,280
I want to resign from my role as the CEO.

440
00:34:02,280 --> 00:34:05,200
If you resign, what will become of Empire?

441
00:34:05,200 --> 00:34:07,200
But I have a right to live my own life!

442
00:34:07,200 --> 00:34:07,960
I won’t allow it!

443
00:34:09,400 --> 00:34:12,560
Did you even think about the consequences of your actions?

444
00:34:12,840 --> 00:34:13,840
Did you?

445
00:34:14,840 --> 00:34:17,160
I want to work on
a gated community project with Tim.

446
00:34:20,800 --> 00:34:24,280
And I want it to be
a separate business from our family’s.

447
00:34:25,600 --> 00:34:28,560
Every baht spent on this project
will come from my own pocket.

448
00:34:34,560 --> 00:34:36,480
I really want to do this with Tim.

449
00:34:42,040 --> 00:34:48,400
Are you saying you no longer want to
take over my role when I can’t?

450
00:34:53,000 --> 00:34:58,840
I ask for permission to take responsibility
only for Empire as a mall.

451
00:35:01,680 --> 00:35:03,840
But the rest of our family’s businesses,

452
00:35:05,720 --> 00:35:06,960
I want no part in it.

453
00:35:13,960 --> 00:35:15,760
Thanks for your honesty.

454
00:35:17,400 --> 00:35:19,160
As for whatever project you want to do,

455
00:35:20,760 --> 00:35:22,240
I wish you both luck.

456
00:35:41,280 --> 00:35:44,680
I don’t know when
you threw all your rules away.

457
00:35:46,120 --> 00:35:49,400
But isn’t it obvious that
you’re in love with him?

458
00:35:52,280 --> 00:35:53,560
Once you can admit it to yourself,

459
00:35:59,360 --> 00:36:01,160
this plan of yours will be useless.

460
00:36:02,320 --> 00:36:04,160
You might want to come up
with a new plan for your new life.

461
00:36:09,640 --> 00:36:10,480
What happened then?

462
00:36:14,000 --> 00:36:15,040
You know, baby,

463
00:36:16,880 --> 00:36:18,440
besides executive management,

464
00:36:20,240 --> 00:36:21,800
I don’t know anything about anything else.

465
00:36:26,560 --> 00:36:27,960
Let’s start our own family.

466
00:36:45,200 --> 00:36:46,600
Will you stay and help me out, Tim?

467
00:36:47,960 --> 00:36:49,360
I really want to do this with you.

468
00:36:53,960 --> 00:36:55,720
You might have had
two options before this:

469
00:36:56,840 --> 00:37:00,640
bring back your old family
or start a new one with Pai.

470
00:37:03,240 --> 00:37:07,680
But maybe there’s a third option
where you can keep both.

471
00:37:16,200 --> 00:37:17,280
Aren’t you scared?

472
00:37:19,760 --> 00:37:21,560
If you chose me and it didn’t work out,

473
00:37:23,880 --> 00:37:25,840
you’d lose everything you’ve built
with your family.

474
00:37:29,960 --> 00:37:32,640
I’d lose everything but still have you.

475
00:37:33,400 --> 00:37:35,440
I’ll always choose you.

476
00:37:49,840 --> 00:37:51,880
Then I choose you, too.

477
00:38:01,840 --> 00:38:03,200
TIM AND PAI’S HOME PROJECT

478
00:38:03,200 --> 00:38:06,960
Are you agreeing to work on this
gated community project with me?

479
00:38:09,960 --> 00:38:10,720
Thank you.

480
00:38:17,600 --> 00:38:19,200
I love you so much.

481
00:38:19,200 --> 00:38:20,760
I love you, too.

482
00:38:35,440 --> 00:38:36,520
Morning, North.

483
00:38:45,520 --> 00:38:47,560
Shall we go to work early today?

484
00:38:47,560 --> 00:38:49,600
I’ve come up with
so many good promotions.

485
00:38:50,320 --> 00:38:53,080
Or maybe you want to play squash today?

486
00:38:53,080 --> 00:38:54,320
I’ll give you a ride.

487
00:38:54,320 --> 00:38:54,720
U.

488
00:38:55,080 --> 00:38:56,280
Can you give me a minute?

489
00:39:34,480 --> 00:39:35,080
So…

490
00:39:36,120 --> 00:39:37,800
I was thinking about us last night.

491
00:39:39,920 --> 00:39:40,560
Me, to—

492
00:39:44,760 --> 00:39:46,440
I’ll admit that…

493
00:39:48,040 --> 00:39:49,720
I really like you.

494
00:39:50,680 --> 00:39:51,560
But!

495
00:39:55,560 --> 00:39:58,080
I just can’t trust you again.

496
00:40:01,120 --> 00:40:02,680
Do you understand?

497
00:40:03,160 --> 00:40:04,720
You were fooling me.

498
00:40:05,520 --> 00:40:06,600
Actually—

499
00:40:11,080 --> 00:40:12,800
You’re a scammer.

500
00:40:12,840 --> 00:40:15,080
I can’t bring myself to trust a scammer.

501
00:40:17,720 --> 00:40:19,080
It’s never going to work.

502
00:40:20,240 --> 00:40:21,600
Do you understand?

503
00:40:24,520 --> 00:40:25,640
Yes, I do.

504
00:40:28,520 --> 00:40:29,520
Okay.

505
00:40:30,160 --> 00:40:31,280
North.

506
00:40:32,520 --> 00:40:33,440
What now?

507
00:40:33,680 --> 00:40:35,720
I’ll do whatever it takes
for you to trust me again.

508
00:40:36,000 --> 00:40:37,600
It’s not gonna work.

509
00:40:38,440 --> 00:40:41,160
I’ll do whatever it takes
for you to trust me again.

510
00:40:43,600 --> 00:40:44,520
Ugh!

511
00:40:46,080 --> 00:40:47,000
Did you hear me?

512
00:40:47,640 --> 00:40:50,520
I’ll do whatever it takes
for you to trust me again.

513
00:40:54,960 --> 00:40:57,840
I’ll make you trust me again.

514
00:40:59,240 --> 00:41:00,080
You hear me, North?

515
00:41:10,160 --> 00:41:10,680
Baby?

516
00:41:10,960 --> 00:41:12,040
Did you even get any sleep?

517
00:41:13,840 --> 00:41:14,840
I didn’t.

518
00:41:16,280 --> 00:41:17,200
I got too excited.

519
00:41:34,480 --> 00:41:37,280
I’ve never seen you
in your work mode before.

520
00:41:37,600 --> 00:41:38,400
You look so cool.

521
00:41:42,480 --> 00:41:43,400
You think so?

522
00:41:46,360 --> 00:41:47,600
You look adorable, too.

523
00:41:52,840 --> 00:41:54,360
Do you have to go to work early today?

524
00:42:27,760 --> 00:42:28,600
Why are you blushing?

525
00:42:29,320 --> 00:42:30,400
Because you look so adorable today.

526
00:42:32,240 --> 00:42:32,840
Hello.

527
00:42:33,160 --> 00:42:35,880
I want North to trust me again.

528
00:42:36,400 --> 00:42:37,760
This is my place.

529
00:42:38,280 --> 00:42:39,880
This is everything I have.

530
00:42:40,400 --> 00:42:44,720
I believe someone as nice as you
would never hurt me, North.

531
00:42:46,800 --> 00:42:48,080
Why did you kiss me?

532
00:42:48,280 --> 00:42:49,600
We’re going to meet Kuea.

533
00:42:49,600 --> 00:42:51,320
I don’t want you acting up
because of jealousy again.

534
00:42:51,320 --> 00:42:51,880
Mama.

535
00:42:52,240 --> 00:42:53,560
I have a boyfriend.

536
00:42:53,560 --> 00:42:57,560
It was too late to back off
the moment I knew I fell for him.

